title: Classic 60s The Beat Goes On (Flac + MP3) JediMaster
description:
"Time-Life Music's Classic '60s: The Beat Goes On features 12 radio staples from the '60s, including "Incense and Peppermints" by the Strawberry Alarm Clock, "Monday, Monday" by the Mamas and the Papas, "I'm a Man" by the Spencer Davis Group, "Do Wah Diddy Diddy" by Manfred Mann, "Bus Stop" by the Hollies, "The Letter" by the Box Tops and "This Diamond Ring" by Gary Lewis and the Playboys. These songs are available on other compilations, but this disc offers a decent '60s rock collection for casual fans." (Gina Boldman - AllMusic)

Nice compilation of 60's oldies. All are ripped in Flac as well as MP3 at 320 kbps.

Enjoy,
